Name: Otravo
Company description: Otravo is a leading European online travel organization. Name: Hamilton Travel
Company description: At its start in 1992, Hamilton Travel had organised about six tours and carried around 250 passengers abroad.  Since then the company has expanded steadily, sending Maltese tourists to more and more new destinations. During 2011 and 2012, 150 tours were successfully organised and the annual figure of Maltese tourists travelling with Hamilton Travel grew to over 20,000.  The most popular and successful tours have always been to Paris and Disneyland, to the UK, Costa Brava in Spain, Sicily and Italy.  However, tours available today range from trips to New York, Los Angeles, Las Vegas, the West Coast and Orlando in America, including cruises in the Caribbean and Bahamas, to Istanbul and Antalya in Turkey, to North Africa, to cruises around Europe and the Mediterranean, and to various other countries, including Scandinavia, Holland, Belgium, Germany, Switzerland, Spain, Portugal, the Czech Republic, Slovenia, France, Italy and the UK. Our offices are situated on the Granaries in Floriana, just outside the capital city of Valletta. In Gozo, we are represented by Links Travel in Rabat, for the convenience of our clients on Malta‚Äôs sister island.  Our staff are highly trained, motivated and experienced in this line of business and we are familiar with the latest technologies relevant to the industry.  We employ the best tour leaders on the island, who are hand picked, trained and assigned to their specialised destinations.  The company now boasts 15 full-time staff, six part-timers and over 40 tour leaders. We keep an eye on the latest trends in international travel, and do our best to cater to market needs.Our motto, which is included in our mission statement, has always been ‚Äúquality affordable tours‚Äù and our aim is being met, as can be evidenced by the positive feedback we receive from our clients. Hamilton Travel, in essence, is an incoming and outgoing tour operator, organising its own tours, constantly in search of great deals with airlines, cruise liners, hotels, cars and coach companies.  We also cater for individual travellers who may opt to travel alone for leisure or business purposes, and are also equipped to help soon-to-be-wed couples organise their dream honeymoon. Flights, accommodation, car hire, trains, football and concert and theatre tickets may all be booked through Hamilton Travel. The company is one of the top three outgoing travel enterprises on the island. Since 1996, Hamilton Travel has been the exclusive Malta General Sales Agent for one of the world‚Äôs top cruise line companies ‚Äì MSC Crociere.  Over 8,000 Maltese people travel on cruises out of Malta each year.  Our company also carries out shore excursions for the foreign passengers on board the MSC ships. We are one of the leading companies in MICE and are the local representatives for several European travel agents for group and individual travel, organising flights, hotel and private apartment accommodation, sightseeing tours, transfers and private chauffeur and self drive cars for people attending MICE conferences. We also provide a personal meet and greet service at the airport or/and sea port. Air Malta, our island‚Äôs national carrier, counts Hamilton Travel as its number one partner in the Maltese travel business, both in the incoming and outgoing sectors. We specialise in outgoing and incoming tours together with ensuring the requirements of individual travellers are met. We are proud to form part of the main tour and individual travel operators in Malta.

Name: GetMyCar
HQ Location: Italy, Varese, Vizzola Ticino, 5 Strada Prov 52, 21010
Company description: GetMyCar is an innovative Car Rental & Car Sharing platform for car owners and users. Our mission is to revolutionize the world of mobility by putting owners with a car that they are not using with individuals and groups looking for a car for short periods of time. GetMyCar was created to innovate usage of one of the most over-rated assets: the car. Research shows that our vehicles spend more than 95% of the time parked up, unused (https://goo.gl/ZduTp1). Despite this fact, their value is constantly subject to devaluation, losing up to 50% in four years and yet there are few alternative proposals that have appeared in the automotive market in recent years. But they all have one thing in common: the fact that by trying to solve a problem they are overcrowding the market without considering the unused resources parked on our streets. Our platform aims to create the space for a community of people interested in optimizing the car as a shared resource, moving away from the idea of ownership of goods towards the concept of use of property that is independent of ownership. At the heart of the sharing economy are shared values and mutual trust. GetMyCar acts as the moderator, defining the rules and adding the guarantees, including insurance and certified locations where the real "exchange" of the car takes place. At the heart of GetMyCar certified locations are the ParkinGO network structures which, thanks to their twenty years of experience, are equipped to check the status of vehicles entering and leaving ". GetMyCar, a young startup aligns with the spirit of sharing, and we believe it is destined to enjoy more and more importance in the global economy. We see it following the example of innovative brands like Airbnb, the peer-to-peer sharing accommodation concept, BlaBlaCar, the most famous car pooling community in the world, and Gnammo, a model of social eating.

While the Icelandic travel industry has grown tremendously in the past decade, a large part of what local companies earn goes to fees for large booking sites. These fees can run up to 40% of the tour price. That adds up!¬† Creating a win-win situation for travelers and tour companies I want to do things differently. Since there is only one of me and my overhead costs are low, I can help travelers save on quality tours and ensure that Icelandic tour companies keep more of what they earn. Unlike the big booking sites, I have no management or team to pay. And no investors are demanding a high return on their investment. It is just me working in my free time on a project that I enjoy tremendously. If you book a trip using my promo codes, I will not receive an exuberant share of the booking amount. My share is only 5%. The travel company gives a discount which reduces the price for travelers. Often this discount is 10%, So the tour company typically keeps 85% of their cost, unlike the 70% left behind when the booking sites have taken their fees. Join the hundreds of people who have been able to save significantly on their Iceland adventure by signing up for the Stuck in Iceland newsletter, which gives you access to dozens of discounts for top-rated Icelandic tours and activities.

Name: ParkFlyRent
Company description: ParkFlyRent takes carsharing to the place where you have to pay the most for your car to be idle: the airport.  At ParkFlyRent, you park for free near Amsterdam Airport Schiphol & Eindhoven Airport. While you're away, we rent out your car to carefully selected travelers. Fully insured, without the hassle. These renters save 25% or more compared to traditional car rental companies.  Parkers even make money as they share in the rental proceeds, on top of guaranteed free parking and a free car wash. Car companies and leasing companies also rent out idle stock through ParkFlyRent.  Most days, 25.000 cars sit idle at and around Amsterdam Airport, while at the same time thousands of rental cars are being rented out at that same location. The production of these rental cars uses vast amounts of resources and simultaneously causes about 102 million kilograms of CO2 emissions. Our dream is that not a single rental car needs to be produced for airports anymore. As we can replace them with carsharing. Aside from winning the Connekt Affiliation Pitches, ParkFlyRent is also winner of the Junior Mercator Award and two-time winner of the ANWB Sustainable Mobility Award. ParkFlyRent is all about sharing: we share the rental proceeds with the car owners, and its profits with the Wakibi foundation who use it to provide microcredit to small entrepreneurs in developing countries.
